body:
Was trying to figure out how to warm the composition cache and it seemed to not be working correctly for some reason and went digging through and I think the cache is being filled with the same composition twice when loading, since `fromJsonReaderSync(JsonReader reader, String cacheKey)` puts the composition with the key `"rawRes_" + resId` and then `LottieAnimationView.setAnimation(int rawRes)` also puts the composition but this time the key is just the `resId` as a string.

```java
public class LottieCompositionCache {
  […]
  @Nullable
  public LottieComposition getRawRes(@RawRes int rawRes) {
    return get(Integer.toString(rawRes));
  }
  […]
  public void put(@RawRes int rawRes, @Nullable LottieComposition composition) {
    put(Integer.toString(rawRes), composition);
  }
  […]
}
```


```java
public class LottieCompositionFactory {
  […]
  public static LottieResult<LottieComposition> fromRawResSync(Context context, @RawRes int rawRes) {
    try {
      return fromJsonInputStreamSync(context.getResources().openRawResource(rawRes), rawResCacheKey(rawRes));
    } catch (Resources.NotFoundException e) {
      return new LottieResult<>(e);
    }
  }

  private static String rawResCacheKey(@RawRes int resId) {
    return "rawRes_" + resId;
  }
  […]
}
```

Here's a screenshot of the cache data after showing one image, preloading two and showing one of those two:
![](https://dsc.cloud/carlosefonseca/Screen-Shot-2018-09-21-12-20-07-B3nHa.png)
There are duplicates with different keys. I think you sound change `rawResCacheKey` to behave the same as `LottieCompositionCache.put()`.
